Money Stuff =0A As a person who writes columns on the internet, I have a lo=
t of sympathy for =0Aboth sides of the artificial intelligence copyright de=
bate: If =0A=0A=0A <> =0A =0A<https://sli.bloomberg.com/click=3Fs=3D825881&=
stpe=3Ddefault&li=3D12455598&m=3D21d6dea82d6b16615cf44233be620525&p=3D01292=
025>=0A=0A=0A=0ADeepSeek distillation=0A=0AAs a person who writes columns o=
n the internet, I have a lot of sympathy for =0Aboth sides of theartificial=
 intelligence <> copyright debate <>:=0A=0A * If you publish words on the i=
nternet, you have some proprietary rights to =0Athem. If somebody else just=
 took my columns and republished them, under their =0Aown name, without cre=
dit to me, and sold ads or subscriptions against them, I =0Awould be annoye=
d. If somebody stole my ideas and changed the wording a little, =0Aand then=
 republished them in slightly modified form, I would be equally =E2=80=94 m=
